    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-12T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-12T04:00:00-05:00" n="730"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5023: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-12T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 12, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 12—5:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My April 12, 9 a.m.<note n="56" xml:id="d730fn56">Not printed.</note> I have just
                    seen <persName corresp="#p_QT1">Quo</persName> who tells me that he has
                    telegraphed again urging <persName corresp="#p_YWW1">Yen</persName> to obtain an
                    interpretation to be used in connection with the agreement if a time limit
                    cannot be obtained. He showed me a number of telegrams from Geneva indicating
                    reactions there. Chinese apparently desire to take advantage of meeting of
                    League Committee which was to have met on the 11th. For the moment interest lies
                    in attitude of League and negotiations here are indefinitely postponed.
                        <persName corresp="#p_QT1">Quo</persName> hopes to have instructions within
                    a fortnight.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LSMW1">Lampson</persName> informs me that he has booked
                    passage to return to Peiping via Nanking leaving here on Saturday April 16th. He
                    has asked me whether I have any plans. I propose to remain in Shanghai until I
                    am satisfied that there is definitely no further need for me to remain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
